# Sass installation on macOS (with Node.js)

1. Opened the terminal on my Mac.
2. Navigated into my cloned repository:
   $ cd alx-intermediate-frontend
3. Created a new directory for the Sass project:
   $ mkdir 0x03-sass_scss
4. Navigated into the new directory:
   $ cd 0x03-sass_scss
5. Installed Sass using npm:
   $ npm install sass@1.63.4 --save-dev
